The best EQ on the play store. I just found this app and am really 
satisfied. The key difference between this eq and the other eqs on the play 
store is that this one does not only use the global audio output for eqing. 
It can connect to apps like Spotify or Blackplayer directly which makes an 
absolutely huge difference in the audio quality. With other eq apps, 
whenever I would adjust a slider it seemed as though the volume of the 
music signal would just drop except for the channel I was adjusting. When 
this eq is directly connected to an app, when you adjust a slider none of 
the other frequencies are affected. It is really great. If you are into 
audio quality but don't like your headphones sound signature give this app 
a go. The only complaint I have is the interface. It took a few hours to 
understand what all the buttons did, but I was able to learn just from 
trial and error.

replyContent: Dear Amanjeet Sokhey, thanks for reporting the issue. We have released a new update in which Dedicated Connections can be completely turned off. To disable this Go to app SETTINGS > AUDIO ENGINE > GLOBAL OUTPUT (mark this option). Hope this fixes the issue.

content: It's really really buggy, but here's the thing - IT WORKS SYSTEM WIDE. It's the first equaliser that worked with Apple Music for me. Interface a tad complicated, and everytime it connects to a music app it detects, the equaliser switches off - hope the developers correct this last issue.

Is working over Bluetooth. The interface is bad some multiple screens or max/mimise subfeature area.   Fixed now: Sadly does not improve the sound quality for me and decrease the sound volume when activated on any equalise change from flat. For me this is deal breaker the sound volume should not decrease if for example i only rise bass and voice, but this app decrease it. Is obvious I can use the input gain but I do not intend to use something that may add negative effects on sound.   Now I use it only on YouTube since Google did nothing for us to use their app for audio only and sound quality is not so great and this improve it a bit. Using on LG G4 and Asus 300N with all other sound processors disabled. It promises to become a great App
replyContent: Dear User, Thanks for reporting to us. For quick fixes we have rolled new update 2.9. In this update, there are two type of connections. 1. Global output with avg results. 2. Specific App Integration (Spotify, Google Play etc) with superior audio results. To connect to specific app, always launch REEQ before source app (feeding source app to REEQ)

content: Very good. I like the customization. I like that you can turn it off if you wish and NO ads! One suggestion for an improvement. I like genre based presets. I can easily understand them. I don't know what the included presets mean. I have to try them all which is very awkward and I can't remember them. How about adding a toggle switch to change the presets to genre based presets. That way we could have both.  Also would be good if I could rename the custom ones. If it has these features I would give it 5 stars.
Best EQ on the play store, love the customization.
